                <note rend="inline" type="source">393.115 President Hoover/34: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to the
                        Ambassador in China</hi> (<persName type="to">
                        <hi rend="italic">Johnson</hi>
                    </persName>)</head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1937-08-31">August 31,
                            1937</date>.</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>198. Your 578, August 31, 10 p.m. General purport of Department’s 194, August 30,
                    4 p.m., has been announced to press here and Department desires that you present
                    note as soon as possible.</p>
                <pb facs="0485" n="477" xml:id="pg_477"/>
                <p>You may inform Foreign Office orally that the note is based on instructions sent
                    you on August 30.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Hull</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
